author: CBS Philly
title: Man Killed During Attempted Robbery In Chester
text:
Man Killed During Attempted Robbery In Chester February 24, 2017 7:20 AM Filed Under: Chester , shooting 
CHESTER, Pa. (CBS)â€“ A man is killed during an attempted robbery in Chester and his girlfriend saw it happen. 
Police say the victim was picking up his girlfriend at her house on the 2600 block of Boyle Street after 10:30 p.m. last night. 
She stepped outside to see her boyfriend being robbed. 
Police say she then witnessed the suspect shoot her boyfriend in the head. 
The suspect is wanted at this time. 
Anyone with any information is asked to call Chester police.
